Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells based on yttria-stabilized zirconia materials have demonstrated a higher level of technology maturity compared to newer materials actively researched to lower the operating temperature.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of thin YSZ electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Yttria-stabilized zirconia-based cells can operate around 600 degrees C and achieve competitive power densities provided the electrolyte can be fabricated relatively thin.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of thin YSZ electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, a 2.5-mu m thick yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte, commercially available, anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell is systematically investigated under various electrochemical conditions, and area of improvements with the electrochemical performance are identified.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of thin YSZ electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell consists of a Ni-YSZ bulk and functional layer anode, YSZ electrolyte, GDC barrier layer, and LSCF cathode.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of thin YSZ electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using humidified hydrogen, the peak power densities are determined to be 0.31, 0.58, 0.96, 1.41, and 1.78W/cm(2) at 600, 650, 700, 750, and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of thin YSZ electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is found that the ceria barrier layer is porous; thus, it is not effective to avoid the formation of strontium zirconate.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of thin YSZ electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is therefore expected that the performance can be improved further if a denser ceria barrier layer can be deposited.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of thin YSZ electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, energy dispersive spectroscopy analysis revealed significant Ce/Zr interdiffusion between the barrier layer and the electrolyte.
Titulo: Impedance analysis of thin YSZ electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
